    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 20 min, remove the trays from the oven</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining dried oregano</strong> over the fries and push them to one side, then add the <strong>mozzarella slices</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] and top each one with a dollop of <strong>tomato sauce </strong>– these are your<strong> saucy mozzarella slices</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to the baking tray with the aubergine, cut side up</p><p>Return the trays to the oven for 4-5 min or until the brioche is warmed through and the mozzarella has melted</p>",
